text: Mariehamm () is the capital city of the Åland Islands, an autonomous region in Finland. As of January 2014, more than 11,400 people lived in Mariehamm. Many ships sail between Mariehamn and the port of Turku. ==Other websites== * infopage Category:Cities in Finland Category:Municipalities of the Åland Islands Category:Capital cities in Europe
